Rating: 4
This was am "O.M.G." recipe. Very good. I did, however make a few "enhancements." I don't like olives, so I omitted them. I used extra garlic, added sliced mushrooms when I was sauteeing the onions, garlic & tomatoes w/ chicken broth (also added a little white wine with this mixture). I used basil in place of parsley (suggested by another reviewer). I used whole wheat penne pasta. Added bite-sized steamed asparagus when I mixed everything together. Sauteed a chicken breast seasoned w/ salt & fresh ground pepper in white wine. When that was finished, I used the leftover liquid from the chicken breast, added a tad of chicken broth to bring it up to 1/3 cup, and used that instead of water to mix with the goat cheese. I sliced up the (very large) chicken breast & added it at the end to the entire mixture. Be very careful mixing the chicken in, as it will fall apart if you mix too vigorously. This recipe is definitely a keeper!

