I agree with the others, easy to make and really tasty. I never use oil packed sun drieds (too much fat for me) but I find in these recipes there's generally enough fat between cooking oil and cheese (I usually add extra cheese--I know, I know! it's fat ;) to make a lovely rich tasting thing. I have added grilled sliced chicken breast on occasion, that was nice. Also nice as is. I use kalamata olives (and more olives and tomatoes than called for), but black brine cured olives, if dry, would be nasty here. Watch out for that! I was very pleased at how the goat cheese melted to make a creamy sauce. I was very skeptical about that...but it was delicious.

